about.description:
atomium is a molecular modeller and file parser, capable of reading
from and writing to .pdb, .cif and .mmtf files.
about.summary: Python molecular modeller (with .pdb/.cif/.mmtf parsing and production)

name: atomium
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "atomium" %}
{% set version = "1.0.4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/samirelanduk/atomium/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4c1858f3463434221944d47f56d971f5998a20fe985278e374a32bcf2420dc9f

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - numpy
    - requests
    - msgpack-python
    - paramiko
    - tqdm
    - rmsd
    - valerius

test:
  imports:
    - atomium

about:
  home: https://github.com/samirelanduk/atomium
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Python molecular modeller (with .pdb/.cif/.mmtf parsing and production)

  description: |
    atomium is a molecular modeller and file parser, capable of reading
    from and writing to .pdb, .cif and .mmtf files.
  doc_url: https://atomium.samireland.com/
  dev_url: https://github.com/samirelanduk/atomium

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jaimergp
    - samirelanduk
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
